{
  "text": "By definition, \u03c0 f k measures how much decrease could be obtained locally along the projection of the negative of the approximate gradient g N k onto the nullspace of J(x k , s k ) intersected with the region delimited by the bounds. This measure is computed in deft_funnel_compute_optimality, which uses lingprog to solve the subproblem [CITATION_1] .",
